  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How can I reset password of Instagram account without email?",
  "response": "If you don't have access to the email associated with your Instagram account, you can still try to reset your password using your phone number or through the \"Log in with Facebook\" option if you previously linked your Instagram account to a Facebook account. Here\u2019s a step-by-step guide on how to do it:\n\n### Using Your Phone Number:\n1. **Open the Instagram app** on your mobile device.\n2. **Tap on \"Forgot Password?\"** on the login screen.\n3. **Select \"Phone\"** as the method to reset your password.\n4. **Enter the phone number** associated with your Instagram account.\n5. **Tap \"Send Login Link.\"** You will receive a login link via SMS.\n6. **Tap the link** in the message to be directed to a page where you can reset your password.\n\n### Using a Linked Facebook Account:\n1. **Open the Instagram app** on your mobile device.\n2. **Tap on \"Forgot Password?\"** on the login screen.\n3. **Select \"Log in with Facebook.\"**\n4. **Log into your Facebook account** if prompted.\n5. If your Instagram account is linked to your Facebook account, you will be able to reset your password from here.\n\n### If You Don\u2019t Have Access to Phone Number or Facebook:\nIf you can't use either of these methods, you'll need to try contacting Instagram support directly. Here\u2019s how:\n\n1. **Go to the Instagram Help Center** on a web browser.\n2. **Click on \"Privacy and Safety Center.\"**\n3. **Select \"Report Something.\"**\n4. **Choose \"Hacked Accounts.\"**\n5. **Select \"My account was hacked.\"**\n6. **Follow the prompts** to submit a request to Instagram for account recovery. You\u2019ll need to provide as much information as possible to prove that the account belongs to you.\n\nKeep in mind that Instagram may require additional verification to ensure the account is yours, which can include submitting a photo of yourself with a specific code, or other personal information.\n\nIf you are unable to recover your account through these methods, unfortunately, you may need to create a new Instagram account. Always ensure that you have access to the email and phone number linked to your account to avoid such situations in the future.",
